parameters.name: BX
parameters.description:
GSE X component of the magnetic-field in nT.                            
      X points from Earth to the Sun.

parameters.name: BY
parameters.description:
GSE Y component of the magnetic-field in nT.                            
      Y is parallel to the ecliptic plane and perpendicular to the            
      Earth-Sun line, positive opposite to the direction of the Earth's       
      motion.

parameters.name: BZ
parameters.description:
GSE Z component of the magnetic-field in nT.                            
      Z is perpendicular to the ecliptic plane.

parameters.name: BTOTAL
parameters.description:
Average value of the full-resolution magnetic-field magnitudes          
      calculated over the averaging interval in nT. Note that this value      
      may differ slightly from the square root of the sum of the squares      
      of the averaged field components.

parameters.name: NPTS
parameters.description: Number of points in the average.
